race.description: Blue Pyrenees Estate Avoca Cup Hcp
race.comment: STATION ONE (5) is the king of the country cups with seven to his name, including a dominant victory in the Gunbower Cup first up, scoring by four lengths. He's a tough horse who lands on speed and can add Avoca to that list. SACRED EAGLE (11) was well supported in the Coleraine Cup last time out, battling on fairly for sixth. Tipping he can improve on that here. STAUNCH (6) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1400m at Sandown-Hillside, beaten 2.25 lengths. Sharply up in trip now but has the ability to figure. WARPARTY (10) has been racing consistently so far this campaign. Won at Morphettville two back which reads well in this lineup.
